result.execSummary:
The disposition of "Other" is used to indicate several different dispositions. The Charge(s)/Sentence(s) and Court Record Events sections of the WCCA record display additional information that must be reviewed in order to determine the exact disposition of the charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: All parties in receipt of doctor's report and stipulate to the findings. Atty Jennifer Rhodes from Corporation counsel present and informs the court chapter 51 will be proceeding. Court ordered case closed administratively.

Defendant Sao V Lee in court with attorney Alexis B Stewart.  Defendant Sao V Lee in custody.  Katherine Halopka-Ivery appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Sworn as interpreter: Mayhoua Moua.

Attorney Alexis B Stewart in court, defendant Sao V Lee not in court, in custody.  Katherine Halopka-Ivery appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Case set for Review Hearing. Interpreter appearance waived for today's hearing. State requests a Contested Hearing on Competency. Court granted state's request. Case adjourned to branch 47.  Hearing scheduled for June 3, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
Report from Mendota received and filed. lr

All parties in receipt of Doctor's report. No corrections or additions. All parties in agreement with the Findings. Court found defendant  not competent to accept or refuse medications prescibed to restore her competency to stand trial.

 The court finds the defendant not competent to proceed but likely to become competent within the statutory time period.  if provided with appropriate treatment, is likely to become competent within 12 months or within the maximum sentence specified for the most serious offense, whichever is less.  The court orders the proceedings suspended and committed the defendant to the Department of Health Services for an indeterminate term not to exceed 12 months, or the maximum sentence specified for the most serious offense, whichever is less.  Order of Commitment for Treatment (Incompetency) signed and filed. Court ordered defendant transported forthwith. 
Case adjourned to 5-19-15  at 8:30 a.m. for review hearing  in Branch 47.  Review scheduled for 05-19-2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Sao V Lee in court with attorney Alexis Bianca Luster.  Defendant Sao V Lee in custody.  Alyssa M. Schaller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Sworn as interpreter:  May Houa Moua.

Defendant Sao V Lee in court with attorney Kevin B. Dunn.  Defendant Sao V Lee in custody.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bm
  Court is advised by the defense there is reason to believe the defendant is not competent to proceed.  Pursuant to Sec. 971.14 (2) Wisconsin Statutes, Court found probable cause and ordered defendant examined by the Forensic Unit.  Order for Examination, signed and filed.   Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Siefert, Branch 47.   Court ordered defendant REMANDED into custody of Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for February 16, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
